PUH-BrianMartell puh_integer_path_proof_lepton_factors_v10.tex- Updated paper, the “integer path” claim for lepton suppression factors f_μ ≈ 1/206.768 (m_μ / m_e) and f_τ ≈ 1/3477 (m_τ / m_e). Critics will call it numerology if it’s just fitted ratios, not a combinatorial count from E8 geometry. The fix: a formal proof that f_g = 1/N_g, where N_g is the exact number of shortest paths in the E8 root graph from the central Cartan chamber to the generation alcove (defined by triality weight k_g = 5 for μ, 8 for τ). Using the E8 adjacency matrix A (edge if dot product =1, for lattice steps), N_g = (A^{k_g})_{0,g} , the (central, generation) entry of A raised to path length k_g. From E8 structure (240 roots, Coxeter graph with degree 14 avg), the path count is the multiplicity in the representation branching:
